<HEADLINE>
<P>
HENRY LOPEZ 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 State Sen. Art Torres is not "the first Latino to win a major party statewide 
race in more than 120 years" (June 9). 
</P>
<P>
 In 1958, attorney Henry Lopez was the Democratic nominee for secretary of 
state. 
</P>
<P>
 Although the entire Democratic ticket swept the state, Lopez was the only 
statewide nominee to lose in November (to the longtime incumbent, Frank 
Jordan). 
</P>
<P>
 JOSEPH R. CERRELL 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
