<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: ENERGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Russia, Oil Consortium Sign Agreement: The government and an international 
consortium of companies will develop oil and gas reserves off Russia's Sakhalin 
Island.The project, called Sakhalin-2, is valued at $9 billion. Officials 
signed the long-awaited deal at a reception at the Russian Embassy attended by 
Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin and Vice President Al Gore. 
Chernomyrdin has also signed $820 million in loans with the World Bank and 
received promises of further support from both the bank and the International 
Monetary Fund. The loans comprise $300 million for highway repair, $200 million 
for Russia's banking sector, $240 million for farming and $80 million for land 
reform. 
</P>
