BRIEFLY: AUTOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 GM Electric Cars Arrive for Volunteer Test Drives: To the tune of "Little 
Deuce Coupe," eight sporty, two-seat, General Motors Corp. electric vehicles 
rolled into the parking lot of a Los Angeles Department of Water and Power 
maintenance facility for testing by 80 Southland drivers, beginning the first 
week in July. The DWP and Southern California Edison Co. will loan the Impact 
IVs over the next six months to commuters chosen from among 10,000 volunteers 
in the Los Angeles area. GM representatives said the company has other 
"parallel" electric vehicle programs in progress and that no specific vehicle 
has been chosen to meet the 1998 deadline to introduce zero-emission cars in 
California showrooms. 
</P>
