</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Volunteers are sought by the Exchange Club Child Abuse Prevention Center to 
work with families where child abuse has occurred or is at risk of occurring. 
</P>
<P>
 The volunteers work as parent aides, teaching the family parenting and 
communication skills, problem-solving techniques, financial budgeting and how 
to find community resources. 
</P>
<P>
 Bilingual volunteers are needed as well as college students and couples. 
</P>
<P>
 Volunteers take three sessions of training. Those will be held July 13 and 20 
from 6:30 to 9:30 p.m. and July 23 from 9 a.m. to 5 p.m., all at 2482 Newport 
Blvd., Suite 7, Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
