<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEPLORING RACISM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The recent fire at the Stanford home in Oak View reminds residents that there 
is a strong perception of racism in the Ojai Valley. Although officials now say 
it was not arson, this incident brought the issue to the fore once again. 
</P>
<P>
 The League of Women Voters of Ventura County deplores hate in all forms. We 
have extended our condolences to the Stanfords, and herein express our concern 
to any person who has experienced racially motivated harassment. We call upon 
all public, civic, professional, service and church organizations and officials 
to make it clear that the Ojai Valley will not allow any violation of personal 
or civil rights. 
</P>
<P>
 DOROTHY ENGEL 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks 
</P>
<P>
 MARILYN P. STEDMAN 
</P>
<P>
 Ojai 
</P>
<P>
 Dorothy Engel is president of the League of Women Voters of Ventura County. 
Marilyn P. Stedman is Ojai Area Director.  
