ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: DANA POINT; HEADLANDS FLOWERS FOCUS OF SLIDE SHOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The wildflowers that grow in the Headlands area will be the subject of a slide 
show Saturday at the Dana Niguel Library. 
</P>
<P>
 The Dana Point Headlands Conservancy, which formed last year to preserve the 
Headlands, will present the slide show at 1:30 p.m. at the library, 33841 
Niguel Road. 
</P>
<P>
 There will also be a preview of items such as hand-painted ceramic plates that 
will be raffled at the group's August fund-raiser. 
</P>
<P>
 The conservancy, which has a mailing list of 600, intends to buy the land to 
prevent it from being overdeveloped. 
</P>
<P>
 Also at Saturday's meeting, the conservancy will hear a progress report on its 
negotiations to buy the land. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the conservancy at (714) 248-5243. 
</P>
