<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LA PALMA; JULY 1 DEADLINE FOR HOSPITAL CPR CLASS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 La Palma Intercommunity Hospital will hold a "heart-saver class" in 
cardiopulmonary resuscitation on July 9 from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. in the main 
classroom of the hospital, at 7901 Walker St. 
</P>
<P>
 The six-hour course, co-sponsored by the American Heart Assn., will include 
adult and infant resuscitation, as well as the recommended technique to clear 
obstructed airways. 
</P>
<P>
 The class is open to the public, and the fee is $25. Registration and fee 
payment are required by July 1. 
</P>
<P>
 People wishing to register can call the hospital's Community Education 
Reservation line at (714) 670-6066 or (310) 921-4120, Ext. 6066. 
</P>
