</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
RESIDENCY VERIFICATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The DMV and INS recently linked up by computer to verify the legal residency 
status of people applying for their first-time driver's license or 
identification card. This cooperation by the agencies is costing the taxpayers 
$1.1 million.There's only one catch: renewals cannot be traced. Would this 
feature have added another $1.1 million to the deal? 
</P>
<P>
 I've never understood how an illegal immigrant could obtain a driver's 
license, or any other state funded service for that matter. Now I know. Lack of 
simple cooperation and common sense. I guess we expect too much from our state 
and federal agencies. 
</P>
<P>
 Wouldn't it make better sense to spend the money for additional border patrol 
to eliminate the infiltration of illegal immigrants before they brave the lines 
at the local DMV? 
</P>
<P>
 I've been driving in California for seven years and have never been stopped. I 
think those odds are pretty good. Don't you? 
</P>
<P>
 BARRY PETERSON 
</P>
<P>
 Yorba Linda 
</P>
</TEXT>
