<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: BARRETT HIRED AS BASEBALL COACH AT CHAMINADE HIGH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Denny Barrett has been hired as Chaminade High's baseball coach, replacing 
Dave Desmond, who left at the end of the 1994 season to become an assistant at 
Valley College.  
</P>
<P>
 Barrett, 29, has served as an assistant at Notre Dame High and at UC Santa 
Barbara.He is currently an assistant with the Van Nuys East American Legion 
team. 
</P>
<P>
 Barrett was an infielder at Notre Dame High and went on to play at Cal State 
Northridge, DeAnza College and Lewis-Clark State College. Track and Field 
</P>
<P>
 Jeremy Fischer of Camarillo High and Cal State Northridge freshman Beth Burton 
will compete in the USA Track & Field junior championships at Florida State, 
starting today. 
</P>
<P>
 Fischer, who has a personal best of 7 feet 4 inches in the high jump and is 
undefeated outdoors this season, will compete Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Burton, who has put the shot 47-7 1/4, will throw today. 
</P>
<P>
 Marty Beck, 24, who finished fifth in the 400-meter intermediate hurdles in 
the USA Track & Field championships in Knoxville, Tenn., last week and has a 
personal best of 49.50 seconds in the event, has been hired as an assistant 
coach at Glendale College. 
</P>
<P>
 After finishing second in the 1990 state junior college championships for 
Glendale, Beck was a two-time All-American at UCLA, finishing fourth in the 
1991 NCAA championships and second in 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
