<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 12; Column 5; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
96 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; OLDER, NOT BETTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Although his coach and the Moroccan players he frustrated last Sunday insist 
Belgian goalkeeper Michel Preud'homme is at the top of his game, Preud'homme 
begs to differ. 
</P>
<P>
 Despite the evidence -- a shutout that included several saves both teams 
deemed world class -- he says his best days are behind him. 
</P>
<P>
 "The good period begins at 26, 27. At least for me, it was like that," said 
Preud'homme, who estimated that a keeper loses some of his reflexes and 
quickness in his mid-30s. 
</P>
<P>
 "I am not better than I was five years ago. I am 35. How can I be better?" 
HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</TEXT>
