WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; MIRACLES ARE RETIRED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LARRY STEWART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Does the U.S. victory over Colombia compare to the U.S.'s hockey victory over 
the Soviet Union at the 1980 Winter Olympics? 
</P>
<P>
 Not according to ABC's Al Michaels, who punctuated that 1980 game with: "Do 
you believe in miracles? Yes!" 
</P>
<P>
 "Because of the year, because of the Cold War and everything else surrounding 
that game, there's never been anything to compare it, and there never will be," 
Michaels said. 
</P>
<P>
 Will his call ever fit another event? 
</P>
<P>
 "I've retired it," he said. LARRY STEWART 
</P>
