<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 12; Column 3; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
237 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; COLOMBIA'S PLAY: 'COSMIC 
DREADFULNESS' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SIMON BARNES, The Times of London 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I would draw to your attention the curious incident of the Colombians at the 
Rose Bowl. The Colombians did nothing at the Rose Bowl.That was the curious 
incident. 
</P>
<P>
 Colombia, favorites to win the World Cup, were beaten, 2-1, by the United 
States in one of the great upsets of World Cup history. The United States, it 
was widely predicted, would be the first hosts to fail to reach the second 
round. Now an advance is assured, but Colombia are surely out of the 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 And they went down in a performance of almost spooky gutlessness, of almost 
eerie incompetence. It was a performance of cosmic dreadfulness; and this from 
the team that beat Argentina, 5-0, in Buenos Aires last year. 
</P>
<P>
 As the game marched on, and the United States were given the freedom of the 
pitch, the Colombians kept their heads down. There was no player with clenched 
fists urging them goalward, no furious demands for defiance. There were no 
players yelling at teammates. There were no players exorcising frustrations in 
bad tackles. The Colombians accepted it all with a bizarre limpness. 
</P>
<P>
 (World Cup USA Chairman Alan) Rothenberg, and everyone else involved in this 
tournament, has a reason to go down on his knees in gratitude to the 
Colombians. Something took the heart and soul out of them. Any side can get 
beaten, any time, that is football's great beauty; but Colombia went down 
limply, reeling, writhing and fainting in coils. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
