<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES AIRPORT; 
SURPRISE CHECK FINDS 19 LAX SHUTTLE VANS UNSAFE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nineteen of 78 shuttle vans inspected Thursday at Los Angeles International 
Airport were declared unsafe and ordered out of service, a California Highway 
Patrol sergeant said.  
</P>
<P>
 The CHP and the Public Utilities Commission staged the surprise inspection at 
the airport shuttle van holding lot at Alverstone Avenue and 96th Street, said 
CHP Sgt. Ernie Garcia.Inspectors examined the brakes, steering, suspension, 
tires, frames and exhaust systems, and also checked to see if the drivers were 
properly licensed, Garcia said.  
</P>
<P>
 Thirty-two of the vans had no violations and 27 others had minor violations 
not considered safety hazards, so they remained in service, Garcia said. 
Inspectors found 74 violations of varying degrees of severity, and 24 of the 
problems involving steering systems, Garcia said.  
</P>
<P>
 In all, 33 drivers were cited for vehicle violations. Four drivers had no 
license in their possession, but it was unclear if they were unlicensed, Garcia 
said.  
</P>
<P>
 In a similar operation recently, citations were issued on 31 vehicles, 10 of 
which were taken out of service, and two drivers were ticketed for driver's 
license violations, Garcia said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
