<P>
SHIPP TO ENROLL AT UC IRVINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Seton Hall basketball player Tchaka Shipp has applied to UC Irvine, where he 
plans to play for the Anteaters in the 1995-96 season. 
</P>
<P>
 Shipp, a 6-foot-8 forward, announced his intentions to transfer to Irvine and 
play for Coach Rod Baker, a former Seton Hall assistant under P.J. 
Carlesimo.Carlesimo was hired as the head coach of the Portland Trailblazers on 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Petrina Long, UCI associate athletic director and senior women's 
administrator, confirmed the school received Shipp's application, adding that 
it won't finish processing the paperwork until late summer. 
</P>
<P>
 Under NCAA rules, Shipp, a sophomore, can enroll at Irvine but must sit out 
one season before playing basketball. He will have two years of eligibility 
remaining. 
</P>
<P>
 Shipp, a former standout at Brooklyn Lincoln High, averaged 2.9 points and 2.8 
rebounds for Seton Hall last season. MIKE REILLEY 
