<HEADLINE>
<P>
SMITH, GRIFFIN NAMED SOUTHLAND CO-ATHLETES OF YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Keith Smith of Newbury Park High and Sara Griffin of Simi Valley High have 
been selected boys' and girls' co-athletes of the year in the Southland by the 
Amateur Athletic Foundation of Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 Smith, who became California's all-time passing leader with 9,971 yards while 
leading the Panthers to a Southern Section Division II championship last fall, 
turned down a football scholarship with Arizona to sign a pro baseball contract 
with the Detroit Tigers.Smith, a shortstop who batted .352, was drafted in the 
fifth round. 
</P>
<P>
 Griffin, a senior pitcher who will attend Michigan, was 21-2 with 16 shutouts 
and an 0.15 earned-run average. Griffin twice was selected state player of the 
year by Cal-Hi Sports. Griffin's four-year record was 63-6 with 43 shutouts and 
five no-hitters. 
</P>
