<HEADLINE>
<P>
EX-PROFESSOR SENTENCED TO 12 YEARS FOR MOLESTATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANNA CEKOLA, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A former university professor was sentenced to 12 years in state prison 
Wednesday in a sexual molestation case that developed after photographs showing 
graphic abuse of a Newport Beach girl were found discarded on a Los Angeles 
street. 
</P>
<P>
 Ronald Ruskjer, 44, a onetime faculty member at Loma Linda University's School 
of Public Health, apologized for the crime during a statement before a San 
Bernardino Superior Court judge. 
</P>
<P>
 His girlfriend, Evelyn (Evie) Bacilio, 33, a former secretary for an Ontario 
medical supply company, was sentenced Tuesday to six years in prison after 
begging forgiveness from the child's parents. 
</P>
<P>
 Ruskjer and Bacilio pleaded guilty in April to multiple felony counts of 
sexually abusing the 4-year-old girl and taking sexually explicit photographs 
of her. The defendants, who lived in the San Bernardino County community of 
Grand Terrace, were arrested Oct. 8 after tipsters identified them as the 
suspects in the case. 
</P>
<P>
 The case began to unfold in October when someone turned over to police 11 
photographs that had been found on the street. Police believe that the photos 
were thrown from Ruskjer's car by someone who had stolen the vehicle. 
</P>
<P>
 Although state law prohibits distributing pictures showing sex with children, 
police won court permission to release three edited photos to the news media in 
the hope that someone would recognize the adults or the girl. 
</P>
<P>
 Within hours, police received about 40 calls identifying Ruskjer and Bacilio 
as the suspects. Other tips led authorities to the identity of the girl. Police 
arrested Ruskjer in Detroit. Bacilio was arrested in Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities said the photographs were taken Jan. 9, 1993, at Ruskjer's home 
while Bacilio was baby-sitting the child. Detectives say the girl has no memory 
of being assaulted. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Associated Press contributed to this story. 
</P>
</TEXT>
