<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: CALABASAS; CITIES OFFER SUMMER BUSES TO THE BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KURT PITZER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Surfers and swimmers can take city-sponsored buses to Zuma Beach from 
Calabasas, Agoura Hills and Westlake Village starting Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 A school bus will leave Westlake Village every morning except Sundays through 
Sept. 3, and make various stops in that city and Agoura Hills.Rides cost 50 
cents. 
</P>
<P>
 Calabasas is offering free trips four times every day except Sundays from 
Calabasas High School to Zuma Beach, with five stops in between. 
</P>
<P>
 "People are thrilled about it," said Amy Jones, recreation coordinator for 
Calabasas. "We're seeing people of all ages taking the bus: teen-agers, adults, 
and we're even starting to get some seniors." Buses will also be available to 
bring summer school students from Westlake Village and Agoura Hills to 
Calabasas High School. 
</P>
<P>
 For information about schedules and tickets, call Westlake Village City Hall 
at (818) 706-1613, Agoura Hills City Hall at (818) 597-7300 or Calabasas City 
Hall at (818) 878-4225. KURT PITZER 
</P>
