<HEADLINE>
<P>
GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: GLENDALE; CITY'S STREET PARTY TO PROMOTE WORLD CUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JENNIFER OLDHAM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Residents and World Cup tourists alike can put on their cowboy boots and kick 
up their heels tonight at a country-Western street party on Brand Boulevard in 
Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
 City officials will close Brand Boulevard from California Avenue to Broadway 
from 6 to 10 p.m. to make way for the nine-piece country-Western band 
Branscombe Richmond & The Renegade Posse. 
</P>
<P>
 The band will perform with Darlene And The Dixie Flyers. 
</P>
<P>
 The street party also will feature a ranch-style barbecue, prizes and 
line-dancing lessons hosted by In Cahoots Dance Hall & Saloon. 
</P>
<P>
 The party is the second in a series of three events designed by city officials 
to lure World Cup fans to Glendale to patronize local eateries, shops, hotels 
and theaters. 
</P>
<P>
 To kick off World Cup festivities, the city presented a soccer dribbling 
event, which drew crowds of residents to watch participants kick a soccer ball 
for one-tenth of a mile each around an 18-mile course that spanned the city. 
</P>
<P>
 The third and final World Cup promotional event in Glendale will be a cruise 
night from 6 p.m. to 10 p.m. on July 15. This street party also will be held on 
Brand Boulevard between California Avenue and Broadway and will feature Dick 
Dale and Big Sandy and his Fly-Rite Boys. JENNIFER OLDHAM 
</P>
</TEXT>
