<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: PACOIMA; 3-DAY UNITY DAY FAIR IS SCHEDULED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIC SLATER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In an effort to build goodwill throughout the community and the entire San 
Fernando Valley, Pacoima will hold its third annual Unity Day Fair today, 
Saturday and Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're trying to show the rest of the San Fernando Valley we can live 
together," Pacoima Chamber of Commerce spokeswoman Beatrice Hines said. 
</P>
<P>
 The festivities, sponsored by the chamber and the Los Angeles Department of 
Parks and Recreation, will kick off today at 4 p.m. at Hubert Humphrey Park 
with live entertainment, carnival rides, dancers and ethnic foods to show off 
the community's cultural diversity. 
</P>
<P>
 The event runs until 10 p.m. today and from 10 a.m. to 10 p.m. Saturday and 
Sunday. It will include speeches and appearances by community leaders, elected 
officials and clergy Saturday and Sunday. The event offers the perfect time and 
place to put recent racial tensions to bed and come together in celebration of 
unity, Hines said. 
</P>
<P>
 The park is at 12560 Filmore St. For information, call the chamber at (818) 
899-7401. ERIC SLATER 
</P>
</TEXT>
