<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIRE GUTS VACANT APARTMENT UNIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fire destroyed a first floor unit of a vacant three-story apartment building 
Thursday and damaged some others on the second floor, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 About 35 firefighters fought the 4:32 p.m. blaze in the 4200 block of Mary 
Ellen Avenue, said Jim Wells, a Los Angeles City Fire Department spokesman. 
Firefighters extinguished the blaze, but not before it spread to units on the 
second floor, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The building, damaged in the Jan. 17 Northridge earthquake, is vacant while 
undergoing repairs, Wells said. The building was not red-tagged, he added. 
</P>
<P>
 Firefighters estimated the damage at $40,000. The cause of the fire is still 
under investigation, Wells said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
