<P>
 T-Bill Rates Hit Nearly 3-Year High: Interest rates on 52-week Treasury bills 
rose in auction to their highest level in almost three years.The average 
discount rate was 5.04%, up from 5.01% at the last auction May 26. It was the 
highest rate since 52-week bills averaged 5.12% on Oct. 17, 1991. The bills 
carry a coupon interest rate of 5.31%, with each $10,000 in face value selling 
for $9,490.40. Sales totaled $16.59 billion out of bids of $49.98 billion. 
