<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: ECONOMY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Durable Goods Orders Leap: Orders to U.S. factories rose a surprisingly robust 
0.9% in May, the ninth increase in the past 10 months, the Commerce Department 
said. After inching up a mere 0.1% in April, orders for long-lasting products 
soared, with aircraft and parts leading the way, the department said. In 
another report, the Labor Department said first-time claims for state 
unemployment benefits increased by 3,000 last week, from 349,000 to 352,000, 
the biggest increase in six weeks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
