</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Carl's Jr. Tests Green Burrito Food: Less than a year after a brutal boardroom 
fight over a dual-menu concept, the fast-food chain has agreed to test Green 
Burrito products at six locations and is negotiating to add Long John Silver's 
fish meals to eight other outlets.The dual-menu strategy is an effort to carve 
new ground in the industry by giving families a wider choice. The strategy is 
essentially a smaller version of food courts that have been set up in shopping 
malls. Carl's Jr. will add the test to its ongoing value menu concept, which 
promotes good food at lower prices but has not spurred sales as much as parent 
company CKE Restaurants Inc. had hoped. 
</P>
