<TEXT>
<P>
 Time Warner Reaches Out to Kids: The conglomerate will seek to further 
capitalize on the growing children's market by forming a new division called TW 
Kids that will market music, film soundtracks and audio books and eventually 
include a book publishing operation.The division is being formed through the 
company's Time Warner AudioBooks venture and will be headed by that division's 
chief executive, Lori Weintraub. TW Kids is expected to work closely with other 
Time Warner units, such as Warner Bros., Warner Books and DC Comics, as well as 
such licensers as Lucasfilm and Saban Entertainment. Audio products based on 
Saban's popular "Mighty Morphin Power Rangers" program are expected to be 
offered soon. 
