<P>
THE TIMES MUSIC INDEX : COMPANY TOWN; STACKING UP SALES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Total album and single sales of CDs and cassettes for the week ended June 19, 
compared to week-ago and year-ago levels, in millions of units:  
</P>
<P>
 Latest week: 
</P>
<P>
 Albums: 10.9 
</P>
<P>
 Singles: 1.9 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Week-ago: 
</P>
<P>
 Albums: 10.6 
</P>
<P>
 Singles: 1.9 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Year-ago: 
</P>
<P>
 Albums: 9.9 
</P>
<P>
 Singles: 2.1 Hits Magazine Tip of the Week 
</P>
<P>
 Music industry insiders have already moved on from their gleeful reaction to 
Sony's victory in the landmark George Michael lawsuit that sought to release 
the singer from his recording contract in Britain. The latest chatter centers 
around whether Michael, who has publicly stated he will never record for Sony 
again, will negotiate and come to terms with the company before he files a 
legal appeal on the decision.With Michael's inner circle unable to mediate, 
speculation centers around the recruitment of an industry heavyweight. Among 
the names circulating are CAA's Michael Ovitz and attorneys John Branca and 
Allen Grubman. 
</P>
<P>
 Note: Hits magazine is a weekly music industry trade publication. 
</P>
<P>
 Source: Soundscan Inc. 
</P>
