<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: J.M. PETERS REPORTS $3.9-MILLION PROFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 J.M. Peters Co., the regional home builder, on Thursday reported a profit of 
$3.9 million, or 26 cents a share, for its latest fiscal quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Those earnings contrasted with a loss of $1.9 million, or 14 cents a share, 
for the same period last year, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Newport Beach builder sold $100 million of junk bonds during the latest 
quarter, which increased liquidity and allowed it to retire high-interest debt. 
Some of its profit for the period came from the sale of 193 homes, an increase 
from the 17 homes sold in the same period a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 The company reported revenue of $32.8 million for its first quarter, which 
ended May 31. That was an increase of nearly 14% from revenue of $28.8 million 
for the same period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
