<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Anne Michaud, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Humanitarian Award: John Padgett, a family-practice physician assistant for 
Bristol Park Medical Group in San Clemente, has been selected national 
Humanitarian of the Year by the American Academy of Physician 
Assistants/National Professional Group. 
</P>
<P>
 Padgett has sent medical teams to El Salvador, the Honduras/Nicaragua border, 
Southeast Asia, Afghanistan and other needy areas through his association with 
Refugee Relief International Inc., a nonprofit charitable organization. 
</P>
<P>
 As a veteran of the Vietnam War and a former Special Forces medic in Southeast 
Asia, Padgett said he recognized the importance of quality health care. 
</P>
<P>
 "What touched me most deeply was the suffering of the innocent," Padgett said. 
"It became my intention to do something to help them if I had the opportunity." 
</P>
<P>
 With the award, Padgett received $1,000 and a matching contribution to the 
charity of his choice, Refugee Relief International. 
</P>
