190 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cotkin & Collins: Partners in the firm's Orange County law office said 
Thursday that they will sever their ties to the Los Angeles-based law firm in 
mid-July, making official what had long been a separate practice. 
</P>
<P>
 The amicable split-up will create the Collins & Naeve law firm in Santa Ana 
with four partners, seven associate lawyers and a support staff of 12.It will 
continue to limit its practice to defense work in the health care, employment, 
insurance, business and professional liability fields. 
</P>
<P>
 The Los Angeles office, with eight partners and 10 associates, has not 
selected a new name yet. 
</P>
<P>
 Philip S. Gutierrez, a partner in the Santa Ana office, said the two offices 
had become separate practices with little reliance on each other and had gone 
increasingly in different directions. While the Santa Ana office specialized in 
corporate defense, he said, the Los Angeles lawyers have been representing 
corporate plaintiffs and state and local government agencies. 
</P>
<P>
 The split, which becomes effective July 15, will put James P. Collins Jr., 
William D. Naeve, David A. Winkle and Gutierrez in charge of the Santa Ana 
office. 
</P>
