AFI SCHOLARSHIP TO ASSIST WRITERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The American Film Institute has established the Lois Peyser Scholarship in 
remembrance of the award-winning screenwriter who was also the institute's 
first screenwriting teacher. The scholarship will support the work of women 
entering their second year of AFI's screenwriting program. 
</P>
<P>
 Individuals wishing to make tax-deductible donations to the Lois Peyser 
Scholarship should contact Rodney Baker, associate director, major giving, at 
(213) 856-7682. 
