<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Ken Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The California Arts Council has lowered from 4- to 3+ the grant ranking of the 
Orange County Philharmonic Society, which will wait for an explanation of the 
action before deciding what to do, the society said Thursday. "We'll wait and 
see what they say," society executive director Dean Corey said."If we can 
appeal it, we certainly will." 
</P>
<P>
 Council officers were not immediately available Thursday to comment on the 
reduction. In 1992 the society successfully appealed the exact same drop in 
rank to receive a $39,051 grant, more than double the amount it had originally 
been awarded. Before that, OCPS had received the top rank of 4 for five of the 
previous six years. The council uses the rankings to determine grant amounts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
