<P>
 Vote totals -- An article June 17 incorrectly reported the vote on Measure Z, 
a proposed tax to support the Port Hueneme Police Department. Of those casting 
ballots, 64.7% voted in favor of the measure, 35.3% were opposed. The measure 
failed because it did not get the two-thirds majority required for adoption. 
</P>
